<TITLE> IAEO offers food preservation help </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 24 (bdnews24.com) The International Atomic Energy Organisation expressed its willingness to assist the government in food preservation. A delegation, led by its deputy director general Ana Maria Cetto, met with food minister Abdur Razzaque at his office on Sunday and expressed its intention. Cetto said her organisation was eager to assist the government preserving using atomic energy to and prevent attacks from insects and pests. Food grains, potato, tomato and onions could be preserved for long periods in this process, she told the minister. Citing the government's steps to ensure food security Razzaque said traditional preservation system is followed in Bangladeshi warehouses. A proposal regarding the possibility of using this modern technology to preserve food will be made to the Atomic Energy Commission, the minister told Cetto and thanked her for expressing her intent of assistance. bd
